# Save on request

When the user says **save** (e.g. "save", "save this", "save checkpoint", "commit this"), **immediately** create a git commit. Do not wait for them to ask again.

## What to commit

Include all relevant work from the current session, especially:

- `web-main/projects/wagamama-page.html`
- `web-main/css/wagamama-sandbox.css`
- `web-main/js/timeline-squiggle.js`
- `web-main/img/squiggles/wagamama-spine-*.svg`
- Related checkpoint copies under `web-main/checkpoint/` if just created or updated
- Other `web-main/` or `app/` files touched in the same task if part of the same milestone

Do **not** commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).

## Commit message

- One short sentence: what stage/milestone and why (e.g. "Wagamama two spines joined — Part 2 at 561px").
- Optional **git tag** for major milestones: `wagamama-two-spines-v2`, `wagamama-three-spines-v2`, etc.

## After saving

Tell the user:

- Commit hash (short)
- Tag name if any
- One-line revert command, e.g. `git checkout <hash> -- web-main/projects/wagamama-page.html`

## Default

If they have **not** said save, do **not** commit (unless they explicitly asked for commits after each stage in an earlier message).
